# SynapseSpark — Product Requirements Document

> Generated from existing project code | 2026-06-04
> Register: product | Stack: Next.js + React 19 + Tailwind v4 + Motion

---

## 1. Product Definition

### 1.1 What It Is

SynapseSpark is a **synaptic word-association exploration tool**. A user inputs a starting word; the engine radiates five semantically related words outward. Clicking one sets it as the new center, spawning five fresh associations while the prior network fades into an exploration trail. Every visited node stays on the canvas as a clickable footprint, enabling backtracking and re-branching at any point in the session.

### 1.2 Why It Exists

Creative thinking is non-linear. Mind maps force hierarchy. Chat interfaces force linearity. SynapseSpark models the actual drift of associative thought — one word sparks five, five spark twenty-five, and somewhere in the branching an unexpected connection surfaces.

### 1.3 Target User

Creative professionals in flow state: designers, writers, product managers, researchers. They are at a desk, focused, working through a specific creative problem. The tool must feel like a precision instrument, not a toy.

