## 2. Current Implementation

### 2.1 Files & Surfaces

| File | Purpose | Status |
|------|---------|--------|
| `index.html` | Brand landing page with Hero, Bento features grid, How It Works, Stats + CTA | Complete |
| `explore.html` | Full-screen exploration canvas (the actual product) | In progress |
| `src/app/page.tsx` | Next.js entry point — currently renders only a vertical menu component | Scaffold |
| `src/app/layout.tsx` | Next.js root layout with metadata | Scaffold |
| `src/app/globals.css` | Tailwind v4 import only | Scaffold |
| `src/components/ui/menu-vertical.tsx` | Reusable staggered-menu React component | Complete |

### 2.2 Landing Page (`index.html`)

**Sections:**
1. **Nav** — Fixed frosted-glass bar with logo (SVG neural-graph icon), staggered menu toggle, "Try Now" CTA
2. **Hero** — Asymmetric two-column: magnetic typography headline + abstract neural-network SVG constellation with pulse animation
3. **Features Bento** — 12-column grid: main 7-col card (Five-Direction Spread demo), two 5-col cards (Trails, Bookmark+Note), three 3-col cards (Curated Lexicon, Zero Learning Curve, Free)
4. **How It Works** — Dense 2-column grid with 4 numbered steps (01-04)
5. **Engine Specs** — Horizontal scroll track with 4 stat cards (<50ms response, ∞ depth, 375px min width, MIT license)
6. **Stats + CTA** — 4-stat row (2,000+ words, 5 branches, 0 learning time, 100% free) + dual CTA buttons
7. **Footer** — Minimal logo + tagline

**Notable technical details:**
- GSAP 3.12 + ScrollTrigger for scroll-driven reveals and stat counters
- Magnetic typography on hero title (character-level cursor repulsion)
- Spring-entrance staggered text on CTA heading
- Staggered menu system: dual prelayer colored panels (purple gradient) + panel slide with numbered items + text-flip animation on toggle
- Full i18n framework: zh-Hant, zh-Hans, en — with dynamic content replacement via `data-i18n` attributes
- Ripple click effect on all buttons
- Responsive breakpoints: 1024px, 768px, 640px, 480px + landscape phone + pointer-coarse
- `prefers-reduced-motion` honored globally

### 2.3 Explore Canvas (`explore.html`)

Core product surface. A full-screen dark canvas with:
- Dot-grid background pattern with radial mask
- Input area for starting word entry
- Canvas for node + edge rendering
- Bookmark system with note attachment
- Trail preservation of visited nodes

