## 4. Interaction Patterns

### 4.1 Core Loop

```
[Input word] → [5 associations radiate] → [User clicks one]
→ [Selected word becomes center] → [5 new associations radiate]
→ [Prior network fades to trail] → [Repeat]
```

### 4.2 Canvas Interactions

| Action | Gesture | Feedback |
|--------|---------|----------|
| Start exploration | Type word + Enter | 5 nodes animate outward from center |
| Follow a branch | Click/tap candidate node | Center shifts, new nodes radiate (300ms) |
| Revisit trail | Click/tap dimmed footprint node | Node reactivates, 5 fresh directions |
| Pan canvas | Drag / scroll | Follow drag, inertia decay |
| Zoom | Scroll / pinch | 0.3x–3x range |
| Reset view | Double-click empty space | Center to current active node |
| Bookmark | Click bookmark icon | Node adds to collection sidebar |
| Add note | Click note icon on bookmarked node | Inline text input appears |

### 4.3 State Handling

| State | Treatment |
|-------|-----------|
| Empty / first visit | Centered input with prompt: "输入一个词开始探索" |
| Loading (word fetch) | Subtle pulse on center node, no spinner |
| Word not in lexicon | Semantic similarity fallback, silent |
| Error | Toast notification, non-blocking |
| Empty canvas (after reset) | Return to initial input state |

---

## 5. i18n

Three languages, stored in JS object on `index.html`:

| Code | Language | Coverage |
|------|----------|----------|
| `zh-Hant` | Traditional Chinese | Full (all UI strings) |
| `zh-Hans` | Simplified Chinese | Full |
| `en` | English | Full |

Mechanism: `[data-i18n]` attributes on DOM elements, replaced at runtime via `applyI18n(lang)`. Language persisted via `[data-lang]` button state in staggered menu footer.

---

## 6. Technical Architecture

### 6.1 Stack

| Layer | Technology | Rationale |
|-------|-----------|-----------|
| Framework | Next.js 16 (React 19) | SEO + performance + API routes for future backend |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 | Utility-first, design tokens as CSS variables |
| Animation (React) | Motion (Framer Motion) v12 | Declarative, layout-aware |
| Animation (Landing) | GSAP 3.12 + ScrollTrigger | Complex timeline, scroll-driven, stat counters |
| Icons | Lucide React | Consistent SVG icon set |
| Bundler | Webpack (via `--webpack` flag) | Turbopack compatibility workaround |
| Testing | Playwright | E2E and visual regression |
| Package manager | npm | Lock file tracked |

### 6.2 Lexicon Engine (MVP)

- Offline-first: static JSON lexicon bundled with app
- 2,000+ curated words, each with 5–10 semantic associations
- Word lookup: hash-map, O(1)
- Fallback for unknown words: semantic-similarity matching against known entries
- Response target: <50ms per spread

### 6.3 Rendering Strategy

Current implementation uses DOM-based rendering. Plan per original PRD: Canvas + SVG hybrid.
- Canvas: connection lines (stroke-dasharray grow animation)
- SVG: interactive nodes (accessible, styleable)
- DOM: input overlay, bookmark sidebar

